com.camerontec.util.datamodel.fix

Class AbstractUTCEncoder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.util.datamodel.fix.AbstractUTCEncoder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NanosEncoder
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CachingUTCDateEncoder, CachingUTCDateTimeEncoder, UTCDateEncoder, UTCDateTimeEncoder, UTCTimeEncoder

    public abstract class AbstractUTCEncoder
extends Object
implements NanosEncoder
    Base class for UTC nanoseconds encoder implementations.

    Subclasses must provide an implementation for at least one of the following methods:

    • encodeNanos(long, Buffer, int)
    • doEncode(long, Calendar, Buffer, int)

    Further, if a subclass provides an implementation of encodeNanos(long, Buffer, int) which calls doEncode(long, Calendar, Buffer, int) then both must be provided. The default implementation of doEncode(long, Calendar, Buffer, int) throws an java.lang.AbstractMethodError if ever called.

        Encode the nanoseconds offset from the Epoch.

        Note that neither System.nanoTime() DOES NOT guarantee to return nanoseconds from the Epoch. Use WallClock.nanoTime() instead for this purpose.

      • doEncode

        protected int doEncode(long nanosSinceEpoch,
                       Calendar calendar,
                       Buffer target,
                       int index)
        Do the actual encoding.

        The default encodeNanos(long, Buffer, int) method guarantees to call this method exactly once immediately after updating the internal calendar with the current system time.

        Parameters:
        nanosSinceEpoch - Nanoseconds since the Epoch.
        calendar - The calendar against which the encoding is to occur. Implementations may assume that the calendar timezone is set to the target timezone and that the time in milliseconds is set to the number of milliseconds since the Epoch.
        target - The target encoding buffer.
        index - The offset into the buffer at which to encode.
        Returns:
        The number of bytes encoded.
        Throws:
        AbstractMethodError - If the default implementation of this method is called.
